INSERT INTO `blogs` VALUES (1,'Complete Travel Guide to Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar in 2026','<h2>Introduction</h2>\r\n<p>Welcome to our comprehensive guide on <strong>Complete Travel Guide to Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar in 2026</strong>. Whether you\'re a first-time visitor or a seasoned traveler to Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar, this guide will help you make the most of your experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Why This Matters</h2>\r\n<p>Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar, formerly known as Aurangabad, is a city rich in history, culture, and natural beauty. Located in the Marathwada region of Maharashtra, it serves as the gateway to the UNESCO World Heritage Sites of Ajanta and Ellora Caves.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Key Highlights</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Discover the best experiences Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar has to offer</li>\r\n<li>Practical tips and insider knowledge for travelers</li>\r\n<li>Budget-friendly options for every type of traveler</li>\r\n<li>Local insights you won\'t find in mainstream guides</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Getting There</h2>\r\n<p>Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar is well-connected by air, rail, and road. The Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar Airport (IXU) has regular flights from Mumbai, Delhi, and Hyderabad. The city is also accessible via the Central Railway line.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Best Time to Visit</h2>\r\n<p>The ideal time to visit Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar is between October and March when the weather is pleasant. Monsoon season (JulyΓÇôSeptember) brings lush greenery but can affect outdoor activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Local Tips</h2>\r\n<p>Always carry water and sunscreen during summer months. Hire a local guide for heritage sites to get the most out of your visit. Try the local Maharashtrian cuisine ΓÇö especially the Naan Qalia and Shahi Tukda.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>We hope this guide helps you plan an unforgettable trip. For bookings, transport, and more travel tips, explore CSNExplore ΓÇö your complete travel companion for Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar.</p>','Admin','https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1488646953014-85cb44e25828?w=800&amp;q=80','published','Travel Guide','5 min read',NULL,'','2026-04-05 22:19:42','2026-04-05 22:19:42'),(2,'Top Places to Visit in Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar','<h2>Introduction</h2>\r\n<p>Welcome to our comprehensive guide on <strong>Top Places to Visit in Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar</strong>. Whether you\'re a first-time visitor or a seasoned traveler to Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar, this guide will help you make the most of your experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Why This Matters</h2>\r\n<p>Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar, formerly known as Aurangabad, is a city rich in history, culture, and natural beauty. Located in the Marathwada region of Maharashtra, it serves as the gateway to the UNESCO World Heritage Sites of Ajanta and Ellora Caves.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Key Highlights</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Discover the best experiences Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar has to offer</li>\r\n<li>Practical tips and insider knowledge for travelers</li>\r\n<li>Budget-friendly options for every type of traveler</li>\r\n<li>Local insights you won\'t find in mainstream guides</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Getting There</h2>\r\n<p>Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar is well-connected by air, rail, and road. The Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar Airport (IXU) has regular flights from Mumbai, Delhi, and Hyderabad. The city is also accessible via the Central Railway line.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Best Time to Visit</h2>\r\n<p>The ideal time to visit Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar is between October and March when the weather is pleasant. Monsoon season (JulyΓÇôSeptember) brings lush greenery but can affect outdoor activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Local Tips</h2>\r\n<p>Always carry water and sunscreen during summer months. Hire a local guide for heritage sites to get the most out of your visit. Try the local Maharashtrian cuisine ΓÇö especially the Naan Qalia and Shahi Tukda.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>We hope this guide helps you plan an unforgettable trip. For bookings, transport, and more travel tips, explore CSNExplore ΓÇö your complete travel companion for Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar.</p>','Admin','https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1488646953014-85cb44e25828?w=800&amp;q=80','published','Travel Guide','5 min read',NULL,'','2026-04-05 22:19:57','2026-04-05 22:19:57'),(3,'Best Time to Visit Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar','<h2>Introduction</h2>\r\n<p>Welcome to our comprehensive guide on <strong>Best Time to Visit Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar</strong>. Whether you\'re a first-time visitor or a seasoned traveler to Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar, this guide will help you make the most of your experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Why This Matters</h2>\r\n<p>Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar, formerly known as Aurangabad, is a city rich in history, culture, and natural beauty. Located in the Marathwada region of Maharashtra, it serves as the gateway to the UNESCO World Heritage Sites of Ajanta and Ellora Caves.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Key Highlights</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Discover the best experiences Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar has to offer</li>\r\n<li>Practical tips and insider knowledge for travelers</li>\r\n<li>Budget-friendly options for every type of traveler</li>\r\n<li>Local insights you won\'t find in mainstream guides</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Getting There</h2>\r\n<p>Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar is well-connected by air, rail, and road. The Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar Airport (IXU) has regular flights from Mumbai, Delhi, and Hyderabad. The city is also accessible via the Central Railway line.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Best Time to Visit</h2>\r\n<p>The ideal time to visit Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar is between October and March when the weather is pleasant. Monsoon season (JulyΓÇôSeptember) brings lush greenery but can affect outdoor activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Local Tips</h2>\r\n<p>Always carry water and sunscreen during summer months. Hire a local guide for heritage sites to get the most out of your visit. Try the local Maharashtrian cuisine ΓÇö especially the Naan Qalia and Shahi Tukda.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusi